When I visited LA to decide if I should move here I took all my money, all of it... got a hostel on hollywood blvd (it wasn’t what I expected!), and timed the trip to go to Beyond The Streets art festival and see Dudamel conduct at the Hollywood Bowl.

After seeing Dudamel I asked two strangers to take this picture of me because I knew I wanted to live here. In this picture I am truly deeply happy. 

So, tonight is about that. Life rules and life rules. Conducting a party. Thanks for coming to my concert. It’s gonna rock.

I love comedy so much. So many pics to come. Blessed.

My man

Just got back from headlining Outside Lands, exhausted, I pass out on @thisismaryjane_ couch and Bobo climbs up to zzzz with me. I love him so much. He’s the first animal I’ve ever been connected with. He’s 21 and having a really hard time. I’m so sad. He’s so tough.

Bobo was the greatest cat I’ve ever known. He lived 21 years full of biting, stealing food, killing things and antagonizing everyone, especially Archie. He lived well beyond what we thought he would - even in his last days, he was swiping Archie’s food. He was the murderous lord of Brooklyn, the prince of Sunset Park, and finally, a retired hit man in Los Angeles. Bobo - the best bad cat there ever was - you will be terribly missed by everyone who knew and feared you. Thanks for a great run. There will never be another cat like you. 🐾🖤 Bobo 2002-2023 🖤🐾 PS: Thank you to everyone who loved and helped take care of Bobo during his fearsome reign @glazerboohoohoo @leahknauer @aluzer @iamdelharrison @g_rillah @welovedogsla and many more

My friend Bobo died yesterday. I don’t know what to write yet but it’s brutal and I love him. Thank you @thisismaryjane_ for letting me grow close to your cat and call him mine (even though he is no one’s unless he wants to eat your chicken sandwich or your eyes). I’m fucking sad. He rocks. And there will never be another asshole like him who steals bacon off my plate, and draws blood if I try to get it back. I love him so much. Rest in Peace Yung Bo — “What Up Bo?!” Love ya man.
